commText: Ravindra and Gaikwad are at the crease. Ravindra is on strike. Starc will open the attack
Starc to Ravindra, 1 run, short of length on off, Ravindra on the defence gets a thick inside-edge on to the pad, rolls away, they take a quick single
Starc to Gaikwad, 2 runs, short of length on the pads, flicked wide of deep backward square leg and they come back for two, Gaikwad is away
Starc to Gaikwad, no run, short of length and swings back into leg-stump, defended
Starc to Gaikwad, no run, wow! That is a hooping inswinging yorker on off, tails in late, Gaikwad does well to dig it out to cover-point. First time this IPL, Starc has got that to swing so much
Starc to Gaikwad, no run, tight good length delivery on the stumps, Gaikwad gets right behind the line to defend to cover
Rahane has a calf strain so Mitchell padded up and ready to bat at 3. Rahane did not field too.
Starc to Gaikwad, wide, sprays it down leg, Gaikwad flicks and misses
Starc to Gaikwad, no run, that's the one that slants away from outside off, well-watched and left alone by Gaikwad
Vaibhav Arora, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Vaibhav Arora to Ravindra, 1 run, short of length on the stumps, defended to the vacant backward point area
Vaibhav Arora to Gaikwad, 2 runs, fullish outside off, dabbed wide of backward point, wide of third man too, easy couple
Vaibhav Arora to Gaikwad, no run, fullish outside off, Gaikwad tries to steer and misses, does not carry to Salt
Vaibhav Arora to Gaikwad, no run, fullish and angling into the fourth-stump, Gaikwad gets forward to defend
Vaibhav Arora to Gaikwad, no run, sharp short ball and Gaikwad ducks under it
Vaibhav Arora to Gaikwad, FOUR, short outside off, Gaikwad ramps it over short third man, flies to the fence
Starc to Ravindra, wide, slips it down leg, wide
Starc to Ravindra, no run, full on the stumps, driven hard and straight to mid-off
Starc to Ravindra, FOUR, full on the stumps, Ravindra drives hard and in the air, wide of mid-on who is wide, runs away
Starc to Ravindra, FOUR, Starc keeps going full and this is lofted over mid-on, two bounces and over, Starc needs to pull his length back
Now fine-leg in. Both square leg and long-on back.
Starc to Ravindra, 1 run, slower ball full on the pads, flicked to deep square leg
Starc to Gaikwad, 1 run, fullish on the pads, flicked to deep backward square leg and it's just one
Starc to Ravindra, FOUR, poor ball and put away, a slower ball off-cutter is a low full-toss down leg, helped wide of short fine-leg. Expensive over
Vaibhav Arora to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length and sliding into the pads, flicked to deep backward square leg
Vaibhav Arora to Ravindra, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Vaibhav Arora to Ravindra, out Caught by Chakaravarthy!! Straight to long-on. Ravindra takes it on a length outside off, lofts and straightaway he knew he had made a mistake. Did he not know there was a fielder there? Ravindra falls to a cheap score again. Ravindra c Chakaravarthy b Vaibhav Arora 15(8) [4s-3]
Daryl Mitchell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Vaibhav Arora to Mitchell, 1 run, good length outside off, Mitchell drops and runs to cover, is off the mark
Vaibhav Arora to Gaikwad, 1 run, short of length outside off, dabbed down to third man
Vaibhav Arora to Mitchell, no run, full and sliding into the pads, flicked to short fine-leg who makes a good stop
News on Rahane is he can only come to bat after 5 wickets are down or not before 10:50 local.
Vaibhav Arora to Mitchell, no run, slower short ball outside off, Mitchell is on his tiptoes to slash, misses, wants a wide, not given
Rachin Ravindra's batting in PP this IPL Inns: 5 Runs: 106 Balls: 62 Dismissals: 4 Avg: 26.5 SR: 170.9 4s/6s: 14/5
Anukul Roy, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Anukul Roy to Gaikwad, FOUR, beautiful shot. Tossed up full outside off, Gaikwad gets forward to drive wide of extra-cover, along the ground and all timing
Anukul Roy to Gaikwad, no run, skidder on a good length on leg-stump, turned to square leg and Mitchell sends Gaikwad back

Anukul Roy to Gaikwad, no run, Salt goes "ahhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh" for the LBW appeal, umpire Anil Chaudhary does not give it and Shreyas takes the review, quicker and fuller on the stumps, Gaikwad gets forward to defend, gets an inside-edge onto the pads, clear inside-edge and that's a poor review
Anukul Roy to Gaikwad, FOUR, nice, flat and fast, angling into leg-stump, Gaikwad makes room and steers wide of backward point, right into the gap
Anukul Roy to Gaikwad, FOUR, this is excellent from Gaikwad, he makes room outside the leg-stump and drives the full ball from there, wide of extra-cover and Starc has no chance at long-off
Anukul Roy to Gaikwad, no run, short and wide outside off, poor ball, but cut straight to the fielder at backward point
Vaibhav Arora to Mitchell, 1 run, good length sliding into the pads, flicked to deep backward square leg
Vaibhav Arora to Gaikwad, 1 run, full on the stumps, clipped to deep backward square leg

Vaibhav Arora to Mitchell, 1 run, dropped by Ramandeep at deep backward square leg, short of length and Mitchell whips that in the air, Ramandeep sprints, gets both hands but drops it, should have been taken

Vaibhav Arora to Gaikwad, FOUR, what timing. Fullish outside off, Gaikwad opens the face of the bat and punches the square drive wide of backward point, races away, stayed beside the line and put it away
Mitchell Starc's bowling in PP this IPL Overs: 9 Runs: 90 Wkts: 2 ER: 10.00
Vaibhav Arora to Gaikwad, FOUR, poor ball and Gaikwad does not miss out, slower and short outside off, cut away in the air, wide of deep backward point though
Vaibhav Arora to Gaikwad, no run, back of a length and tight on off, solid back foot block
Powerplay scores against KKR this IPL 1/65 by SRH 1/61 by RCB 4/51 by DC 1/52 by CSK*

Powerplay summary -- Steady start from CSK -- KKR start off with two quiet overs -- Ravindra breaks free with two fours off Starc -- Arora removes Ravindra for 15 (3.2) -- Starc looks in some discomfort on the field -- Gaikwad hits three fours in Anukul's first over
Sunil Narine, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Narine to Mitchell, 1 run, tossed up full on the stumps, Mitchell shuffles across and looks to paddle, gets a bit of bat on that and it runs away to short fine-leg
Narine to Gaikwad, no run, slower and good length outside off, Gaikwad punches to cover
Narine to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length offbreak on off, drop and run in front of point
Narine to Mitchell, 2 runs, tossed up offbreak outside off, Mitchell sits and paddles it wide of fine-leg for two
Narine to Mitchell, SIX, that's where he is so strong, Mitchell comes down the track and takes it on the half-volley, slams the loft way back over long-on
Narine to Mitchell, FOUR, beautiful batting. Full on off, Mitchell goes for the reverse-sweep and nails it wide of backward point, races away
Varun Chakaravarthy, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, no run, 91.4kph, length ball on middle, sliding in, Gaikwad defends forward
Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, no run, tossed up on middle, turns away slightly, Gaikwad defends forward
Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, no run, 94.9kph, back of a length on off, Gaikwad looks to make room to cut but gets cramped. Ends up chopping it down the pitch
Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, no run, darted in at 106kph. Back of a length on middle, Gaikwad looks to pull but misses. Gets hit on the hip and looks in some pain
Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, 1 run, back of a length on leg, Gaikwad clips it through square leg

Chakaravarthy to Mitchell, no run, 91.9kph length ball turning in towards off, Mitchell gets forward to defend but is beaten on the inside edge before getting hit on the pad. Chakaravarthy goes up in appeal but impact seems to be outside off
Narine to Gaikwad, 1 run, length ball turning into the pads, Gaikwad clips it through midwicket

Narine to Mitchell, 2 runs, 94.5kph length ball on off, Mitchell gets forward and nudges it into the gap at midwicket. He played it quite softly so the fielder had to come in all the way from the boundary. Easy two
Narine to Mitchell, 1 run, 99kph length ball fired in on off, Mitchell dances down, isn't to the pitch and nudges it through midwicket
Narine to Gaikwad, 1 run, 100.7kph length ball on middle and leg, Gaikwad hangs back and works it through square leg
Narine to Mitchell, 1 run, 97.3kph fuller than a length outside off, carrom ball, Mitchell gets forward and knocks it wide of cover
Narine to Gaikwad, 1 run, flat length ball on off, 98kph, Gaikwad hangs back and punches to deep point

Timeout! CSK cruising towards victory at the moment. They have a big advantage of knowing what the target is, so there's no need to go that hard on a pitch where ball-striking isn't that easy. Can afford to just knock it around. There's dew on the outfield too, making it even easier for them.
Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, 1 run, length ball fired in on middle, Gaikwad punches it to long-off
Chakaravarthy to Mitchell, 1 run, 106.5kph length ball darted in on off, Mitchell shuffles across and tucks it through midwicket

Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, leg byes, 2 runs, dragged down short on leg stump, Gaikwad looks to pull but the ball holds in the pitch. As a result, he's early through the shot and misses. It goes off his thigh pad past the keeper
Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, 2 runs, length ball fired in on the pads, Gaikwad clips it through square leg
Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, 1 run, length ball sliding in on middle, Gaikwad hangs back and dabs it to backward point
Chakaravarthy to Mitchell, no run, 98.8kph, full ball just outside off, Mitchell gets forward and knocks it to backward point
Andre Russell, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Russell to Gaikwad, no run, length ball just outside off, Gaikwad defends forward
Russell to Gaikwad, 1 run, length ball on off, Gaikwad hangs back and clips it through midwicket
Russell to Mitchell, wide, length ball straying down leg, Mitchell looks to clip it away but misses
Russell to Mitchell, 1 run, back of a length on off, slower one, Mitchell hangs back and pulls hard. Only a single to long-on though
Russell to Gaikwad, no run, full ball on off, off-cutter, Gaikwad flicks tentatively to short midwicket
Russell to Gaikwad, FOUR, 131.4kph, short ball just outside off, another off-cutter into the pitch from Russell and Gaikwad pulls it nicely through square leg. Lovely timing, races away
Russell to Gaikwad, 1 run, 133kph back of a length delivery outside off, Gaikwad cuts through backward point and gets across for a single. Fielder cuts it off in the deep
Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, no run, 92.6kph length ball on off, turning away, Gaikwad goes back and punches to short cover
Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, 1 run, back of a length on off, 97.4kph, Gaikwad hangs back and pulls to deep midwicket
Chakaravarthy to Mitchell, 1 run, dances down and finds a ball fired in at 107kph. Almost gets beaten for pace. The bat comes down just in time as he squeezes it off a thick inside edge behind square

Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, 2 runs, streaky runs for Gaikwad, but it takes him to fifty! The whistles get louder at Chepauk. Length ball on off, turning in, he gets forward to defend and it takes an inside edge past leg stump
Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, 1 run, full outside off, driven to sweeper cover
Chakaravarthy to Mitchell, 2 runs, 99.7kph length ball fired in on off and middle, Mitchell bends across and scoops it fine. Charges back for two as the fielder cuts it off
Sunil Narine [2.0-0-21-0] is back into the attack
Narine to Gaikwad, no run, fuller than a length on off, off-spinner, Gaikwad defends forward
Narine to Gaikwad, 1 run, overpitched on leg stump, Gaikwad squeezes it to long-on
Narine to Mitchell, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Narine to Mitchell, out Bowled!! Right through the gate! Mitchell dances down for a lofted shot, isn't quite to the pitch of this off-break and it turns between bat and pad before crashing into middle. Narine punches the air and Mitchell nods his head to acknowledge that he was completely done in there. Mitchell b Narine 25(19) [4s-1 6s-1]
Half-century for CSK captain in IPL \n21 - MS Dhoni \n1 - Ruturaj Gaikwad*
Crowd is buzzing with Dube coming to the middle. One slip in place
Shivam Dube, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Narine to Shivam Dube, no run, flat on middle and leg, back of a length, Dube tucks it to short midwicket
Narine to Shivam Dube, 1 run, length ball on middle and leg, off-break from Narine, Dube hangs back and punches to long-on
Narine to Gaikwad, 1 run, tossed up on off, Gaikwad gets forward and knocks it to long-on
Daryl Mitchell vs Narine in T20s Runs: 17 Balls: 11 two dismissals Avg: 8.50
Daryl Mitchell in IPL 2024 so far 22 (18) vs RCB 24* (20) vs GT 34 (26) vs DC 13 (11) vs SRH 25 (19) vs KKR*

Highlights (Overs 7-13) -> A steady partnership builds between Gaikwad and Mitchell -> Sensible batting by CSK's top-order, nurdling the ball around, dealing in singles -> 50-run stand up between Gaikwad and Mitchell for the second wicket -> Gaikwad notches up his first fifty of the season -> Narine goes through the gates of Mitchell, better late than never -> CSK in control of the chase with only 39 required off 42 deliveries
Mitchell Starc [2.0-0-19-0] is back into the attack
Starc to Gaikwad, 1 run, half-volley on the pads, Gaikwad flicks it in the air and it goes on the bounce to deep square leg
Starc to Shivam Dube, no run, back of a length on off, Dube punches from the crease to mid-off
Starc to Shivam Dube, FOUR, short of length around the tummy, an off-cutter that just sits up for Dube and he nails the pull through midwicket. One bounce and over the ropes
Starc to Shivam Dube, 1 run, cracking yorker tailing in on off, Dube does well to squeeze it away into the on-side
Starc to Gaikwad, no run, length ball on the pads, Gaikwad defends from the crease
Starc to Gaikwad, FOUR, back of a length delivery down leg, another poor ball as he strays in line with the off-cutter again. Gaikwad thumps it behind square with an emphatic pull shot
Chants of Dube, Dube
Narine to Shivam Dube, no run, flat on leg, Dube tucks it to midwicket
Narine to Shivam Dube, 2 runs, slightly short on leg, Dube looks to pull but is late on it. Gets it high on the bat and miscues it in the air. Lands safely between long-on and deep midwicket
Narine to Shivam Dube, 1 run, fired in full on off, Dube drives to long-off
Narine to Gaikwad, 1 run, length ball turning in on middle, Gaikwad hangs back and punches it to long-on
Narine to Shivam Dube, 1 run, full toss on off at 108kph, Dube mistimes the drive to long-off
Narine to Gaikwad, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Gaikwad punches it to sweeper cover
Timeout!
Varun Chakaravarthy [3.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Gaikwad, 1 run, flat length ball outside off, Gaikwad hangs back and cuts through point
Chakaravarthy to Shivam Dube, no run, very wide outside off, Dube goes chasing and gets it off the toe-end to short third

Chakaravarthy to Shivam Dube, SIX, again looks to keep it wide outside off, but it's not wide enough to stop Dube from getting hold of it. He reaches out, swings hard and whacks it straight back for six
Chakaravarthy to Shivam Dube, SIX, full and wide, 92kph, and it's another powerful strike from Dube as he reaches out and hammers it into the crowd over long-off. Absolutely nailed on the front foot
Chakaravarthy goes over the wicket

Chakaravarthy to Shivam Dube, no run, review for LBW from KKR! Seemed to have pitched well outside leg. It's darted in from Chakaravarthy, skids through from back of a length and Dube is late on it as he looks to clip it away. As expected, ball is pitching outside leg
Chakaravarthy to Shivam Dube, no run, length ball on off, Dube hangs back and punches it to extra cover
Vaibhav Arora [3.0-0-21-1] is back into the attack
Vaibhav Arora to Gaikwad, 1 run, back of a length on off, Gaikwad punches it from the crease to long-on
Vaibhav Arora to Shivam Dube, no run, good short ball around the head, climbs on Dube who takes his eyes off while looking to pull and gets hit on the glove
Vaibhav Arora to Shivam Dube, no run, again he gets good height on the short ball, it's the slower on this time and Dube is beaten on the pull as it loops over him
Vaibhav Arora to Shivam Dube, SIX, wow that's massive! Length ball around leg, Dube backs away, creates swinging room and smokes it over midwicket
Vaibhav Arora to Shivam Dube, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Vaibhav Arora to Shivam Dube, out Bowled!! Cleaned up! Full and straight at 137kph, in the slot for Dube to slog but he's beaten completely. Off stump goes out of the ground. Shivam Dube b Vaibhav Arora 28(18) [4s-1 6s-3]
MS Dhoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Vaibhav Arora to Dhoni, no run, 143kph, goes for the yorker but misses by a few inches. It's overpitched around off and Dhoni drives to cover
Crowd has gone berserk with the arrival of Dhoni
Anukul Roy [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack
Anukul Roy to Gaikwad, 1 run, massive roar from the crowd as Gaikwad turns the strike over. Length ball outside off, he cuts gently through point
Anukul Roy to Dhoni, no run, back of a length on middle, punched gently to the right of the bowler
Anukul Roy to Dhoni, 1 run, length ball sliding in on middle, Dhoni clips it through square leg
Anukul Roy to Gaikwad, FOUR, short around off, Gaikwad makes room and cuts it away through the off-side ring. Field was up and it races away for four. CSK are back at home, and back to winning ways

23:01 Local Time, 17:31 GMT, 23:01 IST: Don't they just love playing at Chepauk. Especially when the pitch is like the one we saw today, with the ball holding and gripping. The chase was never a problem with CSK knowing that they could afford to take their time as the target wasn't too high. It was a luxury KKR didn't have because they had to assess the conditions on the go, without knowing what total would be enough. Unlike the previous couple of games here, this wasn't a 180-200 pitch, and ball-striking wasn't easy. Rather, the situation and the conditions were built perfectly for someone like Ruturaj Gaikwad who could take his time and rely on timing to do the work. There was dew on the outfield too, making it all the more easier for the hosts who cruised home without really breaking a sweat as they ended KKR's unbeaten run in this tournament.

Shreyas Iyer: It's deafening out here, but I'll try to express. We got a phenomenal start in the powerplay, but we lost consecutive wickets. We weren't able to assess the conditions quickly after the powerplay, scoring runs wasn't easy. They (CSK) know the conditions pretty well, they bowled according to their plans. Wasn't easy (for the new batters) to go after them from the first ball. We were trying to construct the innings, but it didn't fall in place according to the plan. The wicket changed after the powerplay. We were in a comfortable place and we thought 160-170 was a good score, but we lost momentum. We have to go back to the drawing board and got to learn from that. I am glad this happened at the start of the tournament. When we go back, we know our home conditions pretty well. We need to analyse the situations and need to make the best use of it.

Daryl Mitchell: It is always nice to come and play in front of a special crowd and to get the win is cool. The surface was on the slower side, the plan was to take it as deep as you could. [on Narine] He is a world-class bowler and for me it is coming out with plans and put pressure on them, worked tonight and Rutu being there till the end was class to see. I don't mind wherever I bat, I'm here to win games of cricket and it was nice to get the job done.
CSK have won eight of the 11 IPL matches against KKR at Chepauk
KKR at Chepauk in IPL Mats: 14 Won: 4 Lost: 10
CSK results in IPL 2024 \nAt home - 3 wins in 3 matches \nAway from home - 2 losses in 2 matches
Most PoTM awards for CSK in IPL 15 - MS Dhoni 15 - Ravindra Jadeja* 12 - Suresh Raina 10 - Ruturaj Gaikwad 10 - Michael Hussey
Stats by Shashikant Singh

Gaikwad, CSK captain: Little nostalgic for me. Remember my first fifty in IPL, Mahi bhai was with me and we finished the match in same situation. With Jinks slightly injured, I felt it was my responsibility to stay till the end on a wicket which was slightly tricky. Was a 150-160 wicket - if you rotate a little bit and look for boundaries. Wasn't a six-hitting pitch. It is what we've been following through the years. Jaddu always comes after powerplay. With this team I don't need to tell things to anyone. Everyone is in great headspace. You have Mahi bhai still there, you have Fleming still there. I wouldn't say slow start (for him in this tournament). In T20 there are times when you nick off, you get those one-two balls. Sometimes you need little bit of luck to get going. And I feel today it was perfect where I could take my time little bit - something to talk for experts after the game about my strike rate. Good to get the win.

Jadeja, POTM: Always enjoy my bowling on these kind of tracks. Was just looking to bowl in good areas. I've practiced a lot here - if you bowl in good areas, it helps you. Takes time for visiting team to settle down and plan something. Difficult for them to come here and identify the surface. We know the conditions very well.

CSK at Chepauk are just a different beast. Not for nothing do they have the best home record in the IPL. Today the toss also played a crucial role with dew being a factor and batting getting easier in the second half, and CSK had the luxury of knowing what their target was. So KKR's unbeaten run in this tournament comes to an end. That's all we have from here. It's a goodbye from Sagar Chawla on behalf of Siva. See you tomorrow.
